# Delivery Workflow

Progress the project completely and precisely. A change is NOT done until:

1. `npm run check` passes with 0 errors and 0 warnings.
2. `npm run build` succeeds.
3. The affected flow is verified running in the browser (landing -> start ->
   entrance -> playback -> interaction -> end, as relevant).

## Principles

- Keep changes scoped and non-duplicative. Extend existing modules instead of
  copy-pasting logic.
- Leave no dead code, stub, or unused placeholder behind. If you add a seam for
  the future, keep it minimal and documented.
- Use the dedicated layer/engine/data location (see architecture rule). Do not
  invent parallel structures.
- Update todos as you go; do not stop mid-plan.

## MVP vs future seams

The MVP is data-driven (static JSON scenarios). Do NOT bolt LLM calls, content
generation, or Q&A logic into the engine or layers. Such features plug in behind
the `Scenario` contract and feed the same JSON shape.

## Comments

Explain intent/trade-offs only. Do not narrate what the code obviously does.
